{"id":7,"date":"2014-12-09T00:59:03","date_gmt":"2014-12-08T23:59:03","guid":{"rendered":"http:\/\/www.dynamik-beaver-hero-main.dev\/?page_id=7"},"modified":"2026-05-18T16:01:55","modified_gmt":"2026-05-18T15:01:55","slug":"home","status":"publish","type":"page","link":"http:\/\/jc-static-copy.local\/","title":{"rendered":"Home"},"content":{"rendered":"\n<h2>\n\t\t\tWomen of the Ancient World\t<\/h2>\n<h2>\n\t\t\tOTHER NOVELS\t<\/h2>\n<h2>\n\t\t\tShakespeare&#8217;s Queens\t<\/h2>\n<h2>\n\t\t\tThe Queens of the Conquest\t<\/h2>\n<h2>\n\t\t\tWhat they are saying\t<\/h2>\n\t<h4>Philippa Gregory, move over!<\/h4>\n<p>We have a stellar new historical storyteller in the very talented Joanna Courtney.<br \/>How wonderful to find a historical novel brave enough to move from the well-established cosiness of Tudor times to embrace a much earlier period of history &#8211; the Norman era &#8211; and told from a brave and strong woman&#8217;s point of view. &#8216;The Chosen Queen&#8217; reveals the relatively unfamiliar history of an early English Queen in a thumping good read.<\/p>\n<p><strong>&#8211; Julie Houston<\/strong> (author of Goodness, Grace and Me and The One Saving Grace)<\/p>\n\t\t<ul>\n\t\t<li><blockquote><h4>Terrific narrative drive.\u00a0A must read<\/h4><p>&#8220;With lovely writing and a terrific sense of narrative drive, Joanna Courtney portrays an era of change through a story about a long forgotten Queen. In\u00a0<i>The Chosen Queen<\/i>, Edyth is a heroine who inhabits a convincingly re-created historical world, peopled with personalities whose lives leap from the page. Superb!&#8221;<strong>&#8211;\u00a0<\/strong><strong>Carol McGrath<\/strong> (author of The Daughters of Hastings trilogy)&#8221;The story reaches a heart-rending climax. A must read. I loved it.!&#8221;<br \/><strong>&#8211; Freda Lightfoot <\/strong>(author of The Amber Keeper)<\/p><\/blockquote><\/li>\t\t<li><blockquote><h4>Glorious\u00a0story of love<\/h4>&#8220;A glorious, rich, epic story of love, friendship and sacrifice which will sweep you up and transport you to another time. I absolutely loved this and can&#8217;t wait for the next book in the series.&#8221;\u00a0<strong>&#8211; Rachael Lucas<\/strong> (author of Sealed With A Kiss and Coming Up Roses)<\/blockquote><\/li>\t\t<li><blockquote><h4>Highly Recommended Gem<\/h4>&#8220;A beautifully written multi layered tale with a tremendously authentic sense of place and time . . . an epic feel . . . highly recommended&#8221;<br \/><strong>&#8211; LizLovesBooks.<\/strong>&#8220;An absorbing and emotional debut novel&#8221;<br \/><strong>&#8211;\u00a0Candis magazine.<\/strong>&#8220;Absolute GEM of a book! Couldn&#8217;t put it down!&#8221;<br \/><strong> &#8211;\u00a0VictoriaLovesBooks.<\/strong><\/blockquote><\/li>\t\t\t<\/ul>\n<figure>\n\t\t\t\t<a href=\"http:\/\/www.panmacmillan.com\/author\/joannacourtney\"  target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"  itemprop=\"url\">\n\t\t\t\t<img decoding=\"async\" src=\"http:\/\/jc-static-copy.local\/wp-content\/uploads\/pmlogotrans-300x41.png\" alt=\"pan macmillan logo\" title=\"pan macmillan logo\" onerror=\"this.style.display='none'\" loading=\"lazy\" \/>\n\t\t\t\t<\/a>\n\t<\/figure>\n<figure>\n\t\t\t\t<a href=\"https:\/\/www.amazon.co.uk\/Joanna-Courtney\/e\/B00TU2ZVE4\/ref=dp_byline_cont_book_1\"  target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"  itemprop=\"url\">\n\t\t\t\t<img decoding=\"async\" src=\"http:\/\/jc-static-copy.local\/wp-content\/uploads\/amazon-books-200x38.png\" alt=\"amazon books\" height=\"38\" width=\"200\" title=\"amazon books\" onerror=\"this.style.display='none'\" loading=\"lazy\" \/>\n\t\t\t\t<\/a>\n\t<\/figure>\n<figure>\n\t\t\t\t<a href=\"https:\/\/www.bookdepository.com\/author\/Joanna-Courtney\"  target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"  itemprop=\"url\">\n\t\t\t\t<img decoding=\"async\" src=\"http:\/\/jc-static-copy.local\/wp-content\/uploads\/book-depository-logo-200x49.png\" alt=\"book depository\" height=\"49\" width=\"200\" title=\"book depo